lyric:
[ti:如果]
[ar:我]
[00:14.374]Are losing theirs and blaming it on you;
[00:32.899]If you can trust yourself when all men doubt you,
[00:35.704]But make allowance for their doubting too;
[00:37.808]If you can wait and not be tired by waiting,
[00:41.63]Or,being lied about,don't deal in lies,
[00:43.468]Or,being hated,don't give way to hating,
[00:45.818]And yet don't look too good,nor talk too wise;
[00:48.778]If you can dream -and not make dreams your master;
[00:51.978]If you can think -and not make thoughts your aim;
[00:55.128]If you can meet with triumph and disaster
[00:57.238]And treat those two impostors just the same;
[00:59.188]If you can bear to hear the truth you've spoken
[01:01.593]Twiseted by knaves to make a trap for fools,
[01:04.498]Or watch the things you gave your life to broken,
[01:10.03]And stoop and build 'em up with wornout tools;
[01:12.308]If you can make one heap of all your winnings
[01:14.960]And risk it on one turn of pitch-and-toss,
[01:17.368]And lose,and start again at your beginnings
[01:19.518]And never breathe a word about your loss;
[01:21.518]If you can force your heart and nerve and sinew
[01:23.922]To serve your turn long after they are gone,
[01:28.682]And so hold on when there is nothin in you
[01:30.982]Except the Will which says to them:"Hold on!";
[01:33.242]If you can talk with crowds and keep your virtue,
[01:36.692]Or walk with Kings -nor lose the common touch;
[01:39.292]If neither foes nor loving friends can hurt you;
[01:43.247]If all men count with you,but none too much;
[01:46.52]If you can fill the unforgiving minute
[01:47.702]With sixty second'worth of distance run -
[01:49.807]Yours is the Earth and everything that's in it,
[01:51.912]And -which is more -you'll be a Man my son!
